  <h2>Author's Guide</h2>
  <hr>
  <h3>Announcement</h3>
The conference proceedings will be published in the book series of Smart Innovation, Systems
and Technologies by Springer. Normally, papers in this series are indexed by EI. If the paper
is not presented in the conference, the paper will be excluded from the conference proceedings. 
  <h3>Presentation Guide</h3>
<p>
Each presentation has 20 minutes, including preparation. We prepare a PC for presentation in each room.
Please copy the presentation slide (either PowerPoint or PDF format) to the presentation PC beforehand.
If you need any special equipment, please contact iihmsp2018@spcom.ecei.tohoku.ac.jp.
</p>
<p>
All authors are obliged to make a presentation.
If you cannot attend the conference, we are planning to offer remote presentation. Please contact 
 iihmsp2018@spcom.ecei.tohoku.ac.jp.
</p>
  <h3>Preparing Papers</h3>
The papers should be prepared according to 
<a target="_top" href="https://www.springer.com/gp/computer-science/lncs/conference-proceedings-guidelines">
Springer's computer science proceedings guideline</a>.
You can also find the paper templates for 
<a href="ftp://ftp.springernature.com/cs-proceeding/llncs/llncs2e.zip">LaTeX2e</a>, 
<a href="ftp://ftp.springernature.com/cs-proceeding/llncs/word/splnproc1703.zip">Microsoft Word (newer format, docx)</a>
and <a href="https://resource-cms.springernature.com/springer-cms/rest/v1/content/7117506/data/v1">
Microsoft Word (older format, doc)</a>. The paper should be no less than six pages.
Before preparing the paper, please take a look at the
<a target="_top" href="ftp://ftp.springernature.com/cs-proceeding/svproc/guidelines/Springer_Guidelines_for_Authors_of_Proceedings.pdf">
Guidelines for proceedings authors</a>.

<h3>Submission</h3>

      Please submit papers using <a href="https://easychair.org/conferences/?conf=iihmsp2018">EasyChair</a>.

<h3 id="finalpaper">Submission of final papers and copyright transfer forms</h3>
<ol>
  <li>Revise your paper according to the review comments carefully.</li>
  <li>Format your paper according to the Template carefully. You can
find the paper templates for <a href="ftp://ftp.springernature.com/cs-proceeding/svproc/templates/ProcSci_TeX.zip">LaTeX2e</a> and
<a href="ftp://ftp.springernature.com/cs-proceeding/llncs/word/splnproc1703.zip">Microsoft Word</a>. The paper should be no
less than six pages. The paper more than eight pages are subject to
the extra registration fee. Before preparing the paper, please take a
look at the <a href="https://www.springer.com/us/authors-editors/conference-proceedings/conference-proceedings-guidelines">
Guidelines </a> for proceedings authors.</li>
  <li>Download and fill in the copyright form (either in the <a href="CTF.doc">Microsoft Word</a> format
  or the <a href="CTF.pdf">PDF</a> format).</li>
  <li>Download and complete <a href="https://iihmsp2018.github.io/registration.html">the Registration Form</a>.</li>
  <li>Fill the registration form and finish the payment of registration fee.</li>
  <li>Send your final paper, filled
registration form and the scanned payment (in PDF or JPEG format) to us at iihmsp2018@spcom.ecei.tohoku.ac.jp (Before August 15,
2018) (Very important)
</li>
</ol>

